{"id": 231949410, "title": "KDSG confirms killing of five bandits, recovery of arms, ammunition by troops", "text": "The Kaduna State Government has confirmed the killing of five bandits in Kajuru LGA by troops and the recovery of arms and ammunition Samuel Aruwan, Commissioner, Ministry for Internal Security and Home Affairs, in Kaduna, in a statement said the feat was achieved by troops and Special Forces under the auspices of Operation Whirl Punch, OPWP, conducting special fighting patrols in the Kachia-Kajuru axis. \"This was communicated in an operational feedback to the Kaduna State Government. According to the report, the troops embarked on operations to clear the Maro-Enugu axis spanning Kachia and Kajuru LGAs. \"At Dantarau community, the troops made contact with bandits and after a sharp gunfire exchange, five of the criminals were neutralized,\" the statement said. It said the troops also recovered two AK-47 rifles, one locally fabricated sub-machine gun, nine AK-47 magazines, 250 rounds of 7.62mm ammunition, two motorcycles and two handheld radio sets. \"Similarly, the Air Component of Operation Whirl Punch successfully hit bandits camps in Sabon Birnin Daji general area of Igabi LGA.\" According to the statement, Credible human intelligence sources confirmed the successful operation resulting in several bandits being taken out during the mission. Some of the bandits sustained injuries and are reported to be lurking around the general area in need of medical support. \"Locals in the general area are warned to desist from providing medical support to questionable individuals without recourse to the nearest security agencies.\" It said \"Receiving the feedback, the Governor of Kaduna State, Senator Uba Sani, expressed elation at the breakthrough and lauded the troops - under the leadership of the General Officer Commanding, 1 Division Nigerian Army, Major General MLD Saraso - for their determined efforts. \"The Governor further extended commendation to the Air Officer Commanding, Air Training Command, Air Vice Marshall NN Ananaba and his team, for the outstanding contribution to the security of the state.\" The Governor urged the military to keep up the momentum of operations.", "summary": "<img width=\"1200\" height=\"799\" src=\"https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Samuel-Aruwan.jpg\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;max-width: 100%;\" link_thumbnail=\"\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Samuel-Aruwan.jpg 1200w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Samuel-Aruwan-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Samuel-Aruwan-1024x682.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /><p>The Kaduna State Government has confirmed the killing of five bandits in Kajuru LGA by troops and the recovery of arms and ammunition Samuel Aruwan, Commissioner, Ministry for Internal Security and Home Affairs, in Kaduna, in a statement said the feat was achieved by troops and Special Forces under the auspices of Operation Whirl Punch, [&#8230;]</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://dailypost.ng/2024/06/09/kdsg-confirms-killing-of-five-bandits-recovery-of-arms-amm", "url": "https://dailypost.ng/2024/06/09/kdsg-confirms-killing-of-five-bandits-recovery-of-arms-ammunition-by-troops/", "image": "https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Samuel-Aruwan.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 12:17:04", "author": "John Gabriel", "authors": ["John Gabriel"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ng", "sentiment": -0.079}